Moody's expects the company to maintain its strong credit metrics, with a low gross debt to assets ratio of around 30% and a fixed-charge coverage ratio (FCC) above 4x. Aterian had leveraged its artificial intelligence and data gathering algorithms to quickly and effectively produce and bring to market products to sell on websites like Amazon.  At the time of this writing, Aterian is trading for $4.08 and is trailing the S&P 500 by about 95 percentage points year to date.

title: What Is This "Market" That Stock Pickers Keep Trying to Beat?
summary: An index fund is safer, because with an index fund you are diversified and you've minimized your risks.  The more stocks you own (and an index fund represents an investment in many, many stocks), the worse your overall returns will be.  With an index fund you own the good, the pretty good, the average, the below average, and the awful.
